body.p:
When you edit a module after defining the master files, you have the following benefits:
when the module is validated, automatically identifies the master files which include that module and validates all of them;
the Content Completion Assistant presents all the components collected starting from the master files towards the modules they include;
the Outline view displays all the components defined in the master files hierarchy;
the master files defined for the current module determines the scope of the search and refactory actions. performs the search and refactory actions in the context that the master files determine, improving the speed of execution.
